    reveal_role: "Uncover role",
    role_amor_desc: "Cupid awakens only once on the very first night to pair up two players of his choice (possibly himself). Then he falls asleep again.",
    role_amor_name: "Cupid",
    role_das_wilde_kind_desc: "At the beginning of the game, the wild child chooses another player who then becomes his role model. If his role model dies, the wild child becomes a werewolf.",
    role_das_wilde_kind_name: "The wild child",
    role_der_alte_desc: "The old man survives the werewolves' first attack. But if he is chosen as a victim by the village court or killed by the witch or the hunter, he dies.",
    role_der_alte_name: "The old man",
    role_der_baerenfuehrer_desc: "In the morning, if the bear leader is in his sitting position right next to a werewolf (eliminated players are ignored), the game leader indicates this with a bear growl. If the bear leader is infected by the primal wolf, the game leader growls every morning.",
    role_der_baerenfuehrer_name: "The Bear Leader",
    role_der_engel_desc: "If he is eliminated in the first round vote (not by the werewolves), he wins the game alone.",
    role_der_engel_name: "The angel",
    role_der_fuchs_desc: "When he is called at night, he chooses a player and finds out from the game master whether he or one of their two neighbors is a werewolf or not. If there is at least one werewolf in the trio, he can try again the next night. But if none of the three is a werewolf, he loses his ability.",
    role_der_fuchs_name: "The fox",
    role_der_grosse_boese_werwolf_desc: "The Big Bad Wolf is a wolf that kills twice every other night. He first agrees on one victim with the other wolves, then he chooses a second victim alone.",
    role_der_grosse_boese_werwolf_name: "The big bad werewolf",
    role_der_obdachlose_desc: "When you are called, you choose a person you want to stay with. If that person is killed by the werewolves in the night, you will die too. If the werewolves try to kill you at night, you won't die because you're sleeping with the other person.",
    role_der_obdachlose_name: "The homeless one",
    role_der_ritter_desc: "The knight uses his rusty sword to infect the werewolf on his left with tetanus when they eat him in the night. This werewolf then dies the following night.",
    role_der_ritter_name: "The knight with the rusted blade",
    role_der_stotternde_richter_desc: "The game leader and the judge agree on a sign on the first night. If the judge gives this signal after the village's regular vote and the death of a player, the game master immediately conducts another vote without further discussion.",
    role_der_stotternde_richter_name: "The Stuttering Judge",
    role_der_verbitterte_greis_desc: "At the beginning, the game leader divides the village into two groups based on an obvious, binary criterion (e.g. glasses/no glasses, beard/no beard, taller than 170 cm/shorter than 170 cm, gender) - the old man then belongs to one of the two groups. His goal to win the game alone is to completely eliminate the other group.",
    role_der_verbitterte_greis_name: "The bitter old man",
    role_der_weisse_werwolf_desc: "The white werewolf wakes up every round along with the other werewolves and behaves normally. In addition, he wakes up separately every other round and can kill one of the other werewolves if he wants. His goal is to be the only one to survive.",
    role_der_weisse_werwolf_name: "The white werewolf",
    role_der_wolfshund_desc: "When called upon by the game master, he can decide whether he wants to become a werewolf or remain a villager.",
    role_der_wolfshund_name: "The wolfhound",
    role_die_drei_brueder_desc: "The three brothers wake up together on the first night and recognize each other. Otherwise they are simple villagers.",
    role_die_drei_brueder_name: "The three brothers",
    role_die_zwei_schwestern_desc: "The two sisters wake up together on the first night and recognize each other. Otherwise they are simple villagers.",
    role_die_zwei_schwestern_name: "The two sisters",
    role_dieb_desc: "The thief can swap his card with someone else's in the first round.",
    role_dieb_name: "Thief",
    role_dorfbewohner_desc: "The normal villager has no special ability.",
    role_dorfbewohner_name: "villagers",
    role_dorfdepp_desc: "If the village court chooses the village idiot as the victim, they realize at the last moment that it is only the village idiot. The village idiot stays in the game, but loses his right to vote.",
    role_dorfdepp_name: "Village idiot",
    role_ergebene_magd_desc: "If someone dies, the devoted maid can swap her role with the dead person before learning what role the dead person has and continue playing her role.",
    role_ergebene_magd_name: "The devoted maid",
    role_floetenspieler_desc: "The flute player is a separate party and can only win the game alone, unless he is in love. In this case, he wins if only he and the loved one are left in the game. He always wakes up at the end of each night and appoints two players who he enchants with his music. The flute player wins the game alone if all other players are enchanted.",
    role_floetenspieler_name: "Flute player",
    role_gaukler_desc: "Before the start, the game master selects three additional roles, which he places face up in the middle. At the beginning of each night, the actor chooses one of these roles and plays it until the following night.",
    role_gaukler_name: "The juggler",
    role_heiler_beschuetzer_desc: "The healer awakens at the beginning of each night and selects a player (including himself) whom he wants to protect from the werewolves. Even if the selected player is bitten by the werewolves, he or she will not die. It is not allowed to protect the same character two rounds in a row, otherwise they would become immortal.",
    role_heiler_beschuetzer_name: "Healer/Protector",
    role_hexe_desc: "The witch awakens after the werewolves have chosen her victim. She has a poison potion and a healing potion throughout the game. The game master shows the victim to the witch and the witch can heal him (including herself) with her healing potion so that he survives. But she can also use the poison potion on another player. This means there can be zero, one or two deaths in a night.",
    role_hexe_name: "Witch",
    role_jaeger_desc: "If the hunter is eliminated from the game, he fires one more shot in his last moment of life, with which he takes a player of his choice with him to his death.",
    role_jaeger_name: "hunter",
    role_kleines_maedchen_desc: "The little girl is allowed to blink secretly at night during the werewolf phase in order to recognize the werewolves.",
    role_kleines_maedchen_name: "Little girl",
    role_reine_seele_desc: "You will be called that day and everyone will know that you are a villager.",
    role_reine_seele_name: "The pure soul",
    role_seherin_desc: "The seer awakens while everyone else is sleeping and is allowed to choose one person whose role she would like to see.",
    role_seherin_name: "Seer",
    role_selection_title: "Select Roles",
    role_suendenbock_desc: "Whenever there is a standoff in the village between the scapegoat and a person during voting, it immediately affects the scapegoat. He sacrifices himself for the village and is eliminated from the game.",
    role_suendenbock_name: "scapegoat",
    role_urwolf_desc: "He is a werewolf who can once turn a player into a werewolf instead of eating them. He secretly signals to the game master, after the decision of all werewolves, when a transformation should take place.",
    role_urwolf_name: "The primal wolf",
    role_waisenkind_desc: "When called upon by the narrator, the orphan chooses a role model. The orphan takes on the role of role model. Special abilities are not duplicated, but shared.",
    role_waisenkind_name: "The orphan",
    role_werwolf_desc: "The werewolves are called at night by the game leader, recognize each other and agree on a victim, which is then eaten and is therefore out of the game.",
    role_werwolf_name: "Werewolves",
